{
  "texts": [
    "Meanwhile, the adversarial learning strategy achieved the most fair results for all metrics.",
    "S8 and S12 took unique approaches as they proposed new framework for bias mitigation.",
    "Specifically, S12 (Kusner et al., 2017) proposed counterfactual fairness as discussed in \"Research Objective 1: Measuring the Fairness of Education Algorithms\" section.",
    "On the other hand, S8 (Hu & Rangwala, 2020), developed the multiple cooperative classifier model (MCCM) to improve individual fairness in student at-risk prediction.",
    "MCCM consists of two classifiers, each corresponding to a specific sensitive attribute (e.g., male or female)."
  ]
}